line_1: While Aged Doris tares her Silver Locks:
line_2: The Lovely Sisters melt upon the Rocks,

line_1: Breaks the Doors open; snaps the Locks;
line_2: Dauntless as Death away He walks;

line_1: And steep in mountain-mist their golden locks;
line_2: Charm'd round the NYMPH, they climb the rifted rocks;

line_1: Each by her pine the Wood-nymphs wave their locks,
line_2: And wondering Naiads peep amid the rocks;

line_1: And will sing to my lass with the golden locks.
line_2: I'll throw down my pipe, and neglect all my flocks,

line_1: Yet I'll sing to my lass with the golden locks.
line_2: And tho' witlings may scoff, and tho' raillery mocks,

line_1: He's best spent with the lass of the golden locks.
line_2: A fig for his dials, his watches and clocks,

line_1: My lass bears the bell with her golden locks.
line_2: At the park in the mall, at the play in the box,

line_1: While I have the lass with the golden locks.
line_2: Let them rail at the fruit they can't reach, like the fox,

line_1: Strait LYDIA smil'd; the comb adjusts her locks;
line_2: And at the play-house, HARRY keeps her box.

line_1: And tells them as he strokes their silver locks,
line_2: That they must soon learn Latin and to box;

line_1: Thy Eyes like Doves, thy fair intangling Locks,
line_2: Curl'd, and soft as Gileads Milky Flocks:
